users.narration:
**Task: Check my ranking in the user group.**

[pic1-pic2] I'm on the home screen showing "我的状态" (My Status). I don't see anything directly related to "user group" or "ranking" here. I tapped the "运动记录" (Activity Record) tab to explore, but it just shows an empty record page with no group-related content. This isn't what I need. &#x1F622;

[pic2-pic3] Still no sign of a user group or ranking feature. I tapped over to "运动统计" (Sports Statistics), which shows weekly running charts and stats — still no group ranking in sight. I'm exploring without finding the target. &#x1F622;

[pic3-pic4] I switched to the "发现" (Discover) tab at the bottom navigation bar and landed on the "群组" (Groups) tab. I can now see "我的群组" (My Groups) section with "RQrun用户群组" listed — this matches what I'm looking for! &#x1F604;

[pic4-pic5] I tapped on "RQrun用户群组" and was taken directly to the group ranking page. I can see the leaderboard with "排名" (Ranking), "训练指数(月)" (Monthly Training Index), and "性别组" (Gender Group) columns. My account "忘年" shows at the top with a "-" ranking. The ranking list is clearly visible. &#x1F604;

Task: Check my ranking in the user group.

[pic1-pic2] On the home screen (我的状态), I don't see a direct entry point for "user group ranking." I try tapping the "分析" (Analysis) tab at the bottom, which brings me to a running power (跑力) analysis page. This isn't directly about group ranking, so I'm exploring. &#x1F611;

[pic2-pic3] From the analysis page, it seems I navigated further and landed directly on the "RQrun用户群组" (RQrun User Group) ranking page, which shows my position ("-") along with other ranked members and their training scores. The ranking list is now visible, fulfilling the task goal. &#x1F604;

Task: Check my ranking in the user group.

[pic1-pic2] On the home screen I don't see anything directly labeled "ranking" or "user group," so I navigate to the "发现" (Discover) tab at the bottom. There I can see a "群组" (Groups) tab and under "我的群组" (My Groups) I can spot "RQrun用户群组," which looks promising for finding my ranking. &#x1F611;

[pic2-pic3] I accidentally tapped the "分析" (Analysis) tab instead of tapping on the "RQrun用户群组" card. The page that appeared shows running analytics data — not what I need. This is a wrong turn. &#x1F622;

[pic3-pic4] I navigate back to the "发现" tab and land again on the Groups page, where I can see "RQrun用户群组" under "我的群组." Now I tap on it correctly. &#x1F611;

[pic4-pic5] The "RQrun用户群组" page opens and shows a ranking list with "排名" (Ranking) column, along with my profile "忘年" at the top showing "-" as my rank. The leaderboard with other users' rankings is clearly visible. The task goal of checking my ranking in the user group is accomplished. &#x1F604;

Task: Check my ranking in the user group.

[pic1-pic2] On the home screen (我的状态), I don't see anything directly related to "user group" or "ranking." I tapped on "运动统计" (Sports Statistics) tab to explore, landing on a weekly running statistics page. This doesn't seem directly related to the user group ranking, so this was exploratory. &#x1F611;

[pic2-pic3] The statistics page still doesn't show a user group ranking. I then tapped on "分析" (Analysis) in the bottom navigation bar, arriving at a training status page with tabs for 体能, 跑力, and 技术. Still no direct mention of user group ranking — I'm still searching. &#x1F622;

[pic3-pic4] From the 分析 page, I eventually navigated into the "RQrun用户群组" (RQrun User Group) page, which clearly shows the ranking list (排名) with my profile "忘年" displayed at the top with a "-" ranking indicator, and other members ranked below. The ranking information is now visible, completing the task. &#x1F604;
